<p class="intro">Fortune.js is a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Database_abstraction_layer">database abstraction layer</a> for Node.js and web browsers. It includes adapters for IndexedDB and memory, as well as a HTTP listener (JSON & HTML) and a WebSocket wire protocol out of the box.</p>
<p>The latest version is <strong>{{version}}</strong>. Get it from <code>npm</code>, or <a href="/fortune.min.js">download the browser version</a> (exposed as <code>window.fortune</code>):</p>
<pre class="install"><code>npm install <span class="hljs-literal">fortune</span> <span class="hljs-string">--save</span></code></pre>
